(fifthQuint)Yttrium Y 90 Glass Microspheres PET/CT in Imaging Patients With Liver Tumors.

 PRIMARY OBJECTIVES: I.

 To evaluate the image quality of yttrium Y 90 glass microspheres (90Y) PET/CT post SIRT images as compared to technetium Tc-99m albumin aggregated (99mTc MAA) SPECT/CT.

 SECONDARY OBJECTIVES: I.

 To determine the superior accuracy in both distribution and dosimetry of 90Y PET/CT post SIRT imaging compared to 99mTc MAA planar and SPECT/CT imaging.

 OUTLINE: Immediately after standard of care SIRT, patients receive yttrium Y 90 glass microspheres and undergo PET/CT over 30 minutes.

