This clinical trial studies how well yttrium Y 90 glass microspheres positron emission tomography (PET)/computed tomography (CT) works in imaging patients with liver tumors.

 Images produced by PET/CT may provide better information about the distribution of particles, such as yttrium Y 90 glass microspheres, delivered for selective internal radiation therapy (SIRT) compared to the technetium Tc-99m albumin aggregated single photon emission computed tomography (SPECT)/CT images.

